    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Antimony oxide with 70% barium sulfate; not commonly used by artists as it is less inert than titanium white and turns yellow when exposed to sulfur. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047814/Mayer, Dictionary of Art Terms and Techniques (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種含有百分之70 硫酸鋇的氧化銻。因為銻白比不上鈦白的惰性，遇硫又會變黃，一般來說不為藝術家使用。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
